# The cluster

## Three roles, every time Spark runs

- **Driver** — runs your script, owns the SparkSession, builds the plan, decides what to send out — *the project manager, never lifts a box*
- **Executors** — worker processes that hold **partitions** in memory and run the computations — *the delivery drivers, each on their own route*
- **Cluster manager** — allocates machines to the app; hands out resources, doesn't understand the job

## Cluster manager options

- **Standalone**, **YARN**, **Kubernetes**, or **local mode** (driver + executors in one JVM on your laptop)
